." Man page for disasterparty library overview
.TH disasterparty 7 "March 13, 2026" "libdisasterparty @DP_VERSION@" "Disaster Party Manual"

.SH NAME
disasterparty \- overview of the Disaster Party LLM client library

.SH DESCRIPTION
The
.B Disaster Party
library provides a C interface for interacting with Large Language Model (LLM)
APIs, currently supporting OpenAI-compatible endpoints, the Google Gemini API,
and the Anthropic Claude API. It aims to simplify common tasks such as sending text
or multimodal prompts and handling both regular (blocking) and streaming responses.

The library is designed to be relatively simple to integrate and use, leveraging
.BR libcurl (3)
for HTTP(S) communication and
.BR cJSON (3)
for robust JSON parsing and generation.

Key features include:
.IP \(bu 2
Support for OpenAI, Google Gemini, and Anthropic Claude APIs.
.IP \(bu 2
Support for text-only and multimodal (text + image + file) inputs.
.IP \(bu 2
Advanced generation parameters and **Thinking** tokens support.
.IP \(bu 2
Handling of both non-streaming and streaming completions with safety chunking.
.IP \(bu 2
Detailed, cross-provider streaming events via **dp_perform_detailed_streaming_completion**(3).
.IP \(bu 2
Full support for **Tool Calling** (Function Calling).
.IP \(bu 2
Helper functions for serialization and file management.

.SH GETTING STARTED
1. Initialize a context using
.BR dp_init_context (3).
.br
2. (Optional) Enable advanced features like
.B DP_FEATURE_THINKING
using
.BR dp_enable_advanced_features (3).
.br
3. Construct messages using helper functions like
.BR dp_message_add_text_part (3).
.br
4. Perform the API call using
.BR dp_perform_completion (3)
or
.BR dp_perform_streaming_completion (3).
.br
5. Always free allocated resources.

.SH ENVIRONMENT
The test programs and applications typically expect:
.TP
.B OPENAI_API_KEY
.TP
.B GEMINI_API_KEY
.TP
.B ANTHROPIC_API_KEY

.SH EXAMPLE (Streaming with Thinking Enabled)
.nf
#include <disasterparty.h>
#include <stdio.h>

int main() {
    const char* api_key = getenv("GEMINI_API_KEY");
    dp_context_t* ctx = dp_init_context(DP_PROVIDER_GOOGLE_GEMINI, api_key, NULL);
    
    // Enable reasoning tokens
    dp_enable_advanced_features(ctx, DP_FEATURE_THINKING, 0);

    dp_message_t msg = { .role = DP_ROLE_USER };
    dp_message_add_text_part(&msg, "Think deeply about C programming.");

    dp_request_config_t config = {
        .model = "gemini-2.5-flash",
        .messages = &msg,
        .num_messages = 1,
        .stream = true
    };
    config.thinking.enabled = true;
    config.thinking.budget_tokens = 1024;

    auto int stream_cb(const char* token, void* ud, bool final, const char* err) {
        if (token) printf("%s", token);
        return 0;
    }

    dp_response_t res = {0};
    dp_perform_streaming_completion(ctx, &config, stream_cb, NULL, &res);

    dp_free_response_content(&res);
    dp_free_messages(&msg, 1);
    dp_destroy_context(ctx);
    return 0;
}
.fi

